The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control, NCDC, has said that the total number of active coronavirus (COVID-19) cases is now 11,808. This follows the confirmation of 86 fresh cases of the virus in 7 states and the Federal Capital Territory, Abuja. The agency made the announcement on Sunday night via a tweet on its verified Twitter handle. The new figures bring the total number of recorded infections so far to 161,737, with 2,030 deaths and 147,899 recoveries. The tweet reads: “86 new cases of #COVID19Nigeria; FCT-33
Lagos-28
Ondo-11
Kano-7
Akwa Ibom-3
Rivers-3
Kaduna-1 161,737 confirmed
147,899 discharged
2,030 deaths “Our discharges today includes 29 community recoveries in Lagos State managed in line with guidelines”.